After a stakeholders meeting, governor of Plateau State, Simon Lalong, has ordered for the immediate arrest and detention of all community leaders from Bokkos, Mangu, Riyom and Barki Ladi local government areas of the state. The governors’ action followed explanation by the state commissioner of Police, Mr Isaac Akinmoyede that no arrest has been made in connection with the gruesome murder that took place in Kwata Bokkos local government area where  15 people were confirmed killed. The governor said that he is sad over the development adding that things cannot continue this way. After the briefing from the commissioner of Police, he directed that all community leaders should be put in detention. He further stressed that the people should return to their various communities to ensure security at the grassroots adding that if the head of security failed to carry out his order, he will be forced to leave for Abuja immediately and that he (head of security) should be prepared for whatever happens thereafter. It will be recalled that incessant attacks and killings of innocent citizens has continued unabated in the central zone, which culminated to the governor’s action.